   "source": [
    "# Week 1 | Day 3 — Numbers & Math\n",
    "\n",
    "| | |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| **Level** | Beginner |\n",
    "| **Topics** | int, float, arithmetic operators, operator precedence, integer division, modulo, built-in math functions, math module, type conversion |\n",
    "| **Goal** | Perform calculations confidently — understand every arithmetic operator, avoid common pitfalls, and use Python's math tools to solve real numerical problems |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 1 — Numeric Types\n",
    "\n",
    "Python has three built-in numeric types:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Type | Description | Examples |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `int` | Whole numbers, unlimited size | `42`, `-7`, `1_000_000` |\n",
    "| `float` | Decimal numbers (IEEE 754) | `3.14`, `-0.5`, `2e8` |\n",
    "| `complex` | Real + imaginary part | `3+2j`, `1j` |\n",
    "\n",
    "Underscores in numeric literals (`1_000_000`) are just visual separators — Python ignores them."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "age      = 25               # int\n",
    "price    = 19.99            # float\n",
    "ratio    = 1 / 3            # float — any division produces a float\n",
    "big_int  = 1_000_000        # int — underscore is a visual separator only\n",
    "\n",
    "print(type(age))            # <class 'int'>\n",
    "print(type(price))          # <class 'float'>\n",
    "print(type(ratio))          # <class 'float'>\n",
    "print(type(1 + 2j))         # <class 'complex'>\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scientific notation\n",
    "speed_of_light = 3e8        # 300000000.0\n",
    "electron_mass  = 9.11e-31\n",
    "print(speed_of_light)       # 300000000.0\n",
    "print(electron_mass)        # 9.11e-31"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 2 — Arithmetic Operators\n",
    "\n",
    "| Operator | Name | Example | Result |\n",
    "|---|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `+` | Addition | `17 + 5` | `22` |\n",
    "| `-` | Subtraction | `17 - 5` | `12` |\n",
    "| `*` | Multiplication | `17 * 5` | `85` |\n",
    "| `/` | True division | `17 / 5` | `3.4` (always float) |\n",
    "| `//` | Floor division | `17 // 5` | `3` |\n",
    "| `%` | Modulo | `17 % 5` | `2` |\n",
    "| `**` | Exponentiation | `2 ** 10` | `1024` |\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Note:** `/` always returns a `float` in Python 3, even when the result is mathematically whole (`10 / 2` → `5.0`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "a = 17\n",
    "b = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "print(a + b)                # 22\n",
    "print(a - b)                # 12\n",
    "print(a * b)                # 85\n",
    "print(a / b)                # 3.4  — always float\n",
    "print(a // b)               # 3    — floor division\n",
    "print(a % b)                # 2    — remainder\n",
    "print(a ** b)               # 1419857\n",
    "\n",
    "print(10 / 2)               # 5.0  — note the float!\n",
    "print(10 / 3)               # 3.3333333333333335"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 3 — Operator Precedence\n",
    "\n",
    "When multiple operators appear in one expression, Python evaluates them in this order:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Priority | Operator(s) | Direction |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| 1 (highest) | `()` | innermost first |\n",
    "| 2 | `**` | right-to-left |\n",
    "| 3 | unary `+x`, `-x` | — |\n",
    "| 4 | `*` `/` `//` `%` | left-to-right |\n",
    "| 5 (lowest) | `+` `-` | left-to-right |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mnemonic:** PEMDAS — Parentheses, Exponents, Multiply/Divide, Add/Subtract"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(2 + 3 * 4)            # 14   (* before +)\n",
    "print((2 + 3) * 4)          # 20   (parens override)\n",
    "print(2 ** 3 ** 2)          # 512  (right-to-left: 3**2=9, then 2**9=512)\n",
    "print(10 - 4 + 2)           # 8    (left-to-right)\n",
    "print(10 - (4 + 2))         # 4    (parens change the result)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 4 — Integer Division & Modulo\n",
    "\n",
    "**Floor division `//`** rounds toward **negative infinity**, not toward zero.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Modulo `%`** gives a remainder whose sign always matches the **divisor**.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    " 7 // 2  =  3     -7 // 2  = -4   (not -3!)\n",
    " 17 % 5  =  2     -17 % 5  =  3   (not -2!)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Common patterns with `%`:**\n",
    "- Even/odd check: `n % 2 == 0`\n",
    "- Clock arithmetic: `hour % 12`\n",
    "- Last digit: `n % 10`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(7 // 2)               # 3\n",
    "print(-7 // 2)              # -4  (floor, not truncate)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(17 % 5)               # 2\n",
    "print(-17 % 5)              # 3   (sign matches divisor 5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Even / odd\n",
    "print(10 % 2 == 0)          # True  (even)\n",
    "print(7  % 2 == 0)          # False (odd)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clock arithmetic\n",
    "hour = 14\n",
    "print(hour % 12)            # 2  (2 PM on 12-hour clock)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract digits\n",
    "number = 12345\n",
    "print(number % 10)          # 5  (last digit)\n",
    "print(number // 10 % 10)    # 4  (second-to-last digit)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 5 — Built-in Math Functions\n",
    "\n",
    "These require **no import** — they're always available:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Function | Returns | Example |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `abs(x)` | Absolute value | `abs(-5)` → `5` |\n",
    "| `round(x, n)` | Rounded to n decimals | `round(3.14159, 2)` → `3.14` |\n",
    "| `pow(x, y)` | `x ** y` | `pow(2, 10)` → `1024` |\n",
    "| `pow(x, y, mod)` | `(x**y) % mod` | `pow(2, 10, 1000)` → `24` |\n",
    "| `divmod(a, b)` | `(a//b, a%b)` | `divmod(17, 5)` → `(3, 2)` |\n",
    "| `min(...)` | Smallest value | `min(3,1,4)` → `1` |\n",
    "| `max(...)` | Largest value | `max(3,1,4)` → `4` |\n",
    "| `sum(iterable)` | Sum of all items | `sum([1,2,3])` → `6` |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(abs(-42))             # 42\n",
    "print(abs(3.7))             # 3.7\n",
    "\n",
    "print(round(3.14159, 2))    # 3.14\n",
    "print(round(3.14159, 4))    # 3.1416\n",
    "print(round(2.5))           # 2  (banker's rounding — rounds to even)\n",
    "print(round(3.5))           # 4\n",
    "\n",
    "print(pow(2, 10))           # 1024\n",
    "print(pow(2, 10, 1000))     # 24  ((2**10) % 1000)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(min(3, 1, 4, 1, 5))   # 1\n",
    "print(max(3, 1, 4, 1, 5))   # 5\n",
    "print(sum([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])) # 15\n",
    "\n",
    "q, r = divmod(17, 5)\n",
    "print(q, r)                 # 3 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-11",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 6 — The `math` Module\n",
    "\n",
    "Import once, then use `math.<name>` for constants and functions.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Constants\n",
    "| Name | Value |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `math.pi` | 3.141592653589793 |\n",
    "| `math.e` | 2.718281828459045 |\n",
    "| `math.inf` | ∞ |\n",
    "| `math.tau` | 6.283… (2π) |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Functions\n",
    "| Function | Description |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `math.floor(x)` | Round toward −∞ |\n",
    "| `math.ceil(x)` | Round toward +∞ |\n",
    "| `math.trunc(x)` | Round toward 0 |\n",
    "| `math.sqrt(x)` | Square root |\n",
    "| `math.log(x)` | Natural logarithm |\n",
    "| `math.log10(x)` | Log base 10 |\n",
    "| `math.log2(x)` | Log base 2 |\n",
    "| `math.factorial(n)` | n! |\n",
    "| `math.gcd(a, b)` | Greatest common divisor |\n",
    "| `math.degrees(r)` | Radians → degrees |\n",
    "| `math.radians(d)` | Degrees → radians |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import math\n",
    "\n",
    "print(math.pi)              # 3.141592653589793\n",
    "print(math.e)               # 2.718281828459045\n",
    "print(math.inf)             # inf\n",
    "\n",
    "print(math.floor(3.9))      # 3\n",
    "print(math.ceil(3.1))       # 4\n",
    "print(math.trunc(-3.9))     # -3  (toward zero, not -4)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(math.sqrt(144))       # 12.0\n",
    "print(math.log(math.e))     # 1.0  (natural log)\n",
    "print(math.log10(1000))     # 3.0\n",
    "print(math.log2(256))       # 8.0\n",
    "\n",
    "print(math.factorial(5))    # 120\n",
    "print(math.gcd(48, 18))     # 6\n",
    "\n",
    "print(math.degrees(math.pi))  # 180.0\n",
    "print(math.radians(90))       # 1.5707963267948966"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-13",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 7 — Type Conversion\n",
    "\n",
    "| Function | What it does | Watch out for |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| `int(x)` | Truncates float toward zero; parses string | `int(3.9)` → `3`, NOT `4` |\n",
    "| `float(x)` | Promotes int; parses string | `float(7)` → `7.0` |\n",
    "| `int(s, base)` | Parse string in given base | `int(\"FF\", 16)` → `255` |\n",
    "| `bin(n)` | Decimal → binary string | `bin(10)` → `'0b1010'` |\n",
    "| `hex(n)` | Decimal → hex string | `hex(255)` → `'0xff'` |\n",
    "| `oct(n)` | Decimal → octal string | `oct(15)` → `'0o17'` |\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Float precision:** `0.1 + 0.2` does not equal exactly `0.3` in IEEE 754 arithmetic. Use `round()` or `math.isclose()` when comparing floats."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-14",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(int(3.9))             # 3    (truncates, does NOT round)\n",
    "print(int(-3.9))            # -3   (toward zero)\n",
    "print(float(7))             # 7.0\n",
    "\n",
    "print(int(\"42\"))            # 42\n",
    "print(float(\"3.14\"))        # 3.14\n",
    "\n",
    "print(int(\"1010\", 2))       # 10   (binary → decimal)\n",
    "print(int(\"FF\", 16))        # 255  (hex → decimal)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(bin(10))              # 0b1010\n",
    "print(hex(255))             # 0xff\n",
    "print(oct(15))              # 0o17\n",
    "\n",
    "print(0.1 + 0.2)            # 0.30000000000000004  (float precision!)\n",
    "print(round(0.1 + 0.2, 2))  # 0.3"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-15",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Section 8 — Augmented Assignment Operators\n",
    "\n",
    "Shorthand that reads "update this variable using itself":\n",
    "\n",
    "| Shorthand | Equivalent to |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `x += n` | `x = x + n` |\n",
    "| `x -= n` | `x = x - n` |\n",
    "| `x *= n` | `x = x * n` |\n",
    "| `x /= n` | `x = x / n` |\n",
    "| `x //= n` | `x = x // n` |\n",
    "| `x %= n` | `x = x % n` |\n",
    "| `x **= n` | `x = x ** n` |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-16",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "score = 100\n",
    "score += 10\n",
    "print(score)                # 110\n",
    "\n",
    "score -= 5\n",
    "print(score)                # 105\n",
    "\n",
    "score *= 2\n",
    "print(score)                # 210\n",
    "\n",
    "score //= 3\n",
    "print(score)                # 70\n",
    "\n",
    "score **= 2\n",
    "print(score)                # 4900\n",
    "\n",
    "score %= 100\n",
    "print(score)                # 0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-17",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Quick Reference Cheatsheet\n",
    "\n",
    "### Arithmetic Operators\n",
    "```python\n",
    "a + b     # addition\n",
    "a - b     # subtraction\n",
    "a * b     # multiplication\n",
    "a / b     # true division  → always float\n",
    "a // b    # floor division → rounds toward -infinity\n",
    "a % b     # modulo         → remainder, sign matches b\n",
    "a ** b    # exponentiation\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Precedence (high → low)\n",
    "```\n",
    "()  →  **  →  unary +/-  →  * / // %  →  + -\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Built-in Functions\n",
    "```python\n",
    "abs(x)          # absolute value\n",
    "round(x, n)     # round to n decimal places\n",
    "pow(x, y)       # x**y\n",
    "divmod(a, b)    # (a//b, a%b)\n",
    "min(...)  max(...)  sum(...)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### math Module\n",
    "```python\n",
    "import math\n",
    "math.pi  math.e  math.inf  math.tau\n",
    "math.floor(x)  math.ceil(x)  math.trunc(x)\n",
    "math.sqrt(x)   math.log(x)   math.log10(x)  math.log2(x)\n",
    "math.factorial(n)  math.gcd(a, b)\n",
    "math.degrees(r)  math.radians(d)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Type Conversion\n",
    "```python\n",
    "int(x)          # truncates float; parses string\n",
    "float(x)        # promotes int; parses string\n",
    "int(s, base)    # parse string in given base\n",
    "bin(n) hex(n) oct(n)  # → string representations\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Augmented Assignment\n",
    "```python\n",
    "x += n   x -= n   x *= n   x /= n\n",
    "x //= n  x %= n   x **= n\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Float Precision\n",
    "```python\n",
    "0.1 + 0.2 != 0.3          # IEEE 754 limitation\n",
    "round(0.1 + 0.2, 2) == 0.3  # use round() to compare\n",
    "math.isclose(a, b)          # robust float comparison\n",
    "```"
   ]
  }
